-- Italy’s Merighetti, Swizterland’s Feuz Win World Cup Downhills
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2012-01-14T15:57:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-14/italy-s-merighetti-swizterland-s-feuz-win-world-cup-downhills.html
Italy’s Daniela Merighetti and
Switzerland’s Beat Feuz won  World Cup  skiing downhill races in
their home countries.  Marchetti finished with a time of 1 minute, 33.17 seconds
in Cortina d’Ampezzo to beat Lindsay Vonn of the U.S. by 0.21
seconds. Defending World Cup champion Mari Hoefl-Riesch of
 Germany  was third.  Feuz captured the men’s race in Wengen in a time of
2:35.31. Austria’s Hannes Reichelt was second, 0.44 seconds
behind, with Italy’s Christof Innerhofer a further 0.49 seconds
back in third.  Vonn coninutes to lead both the women’s overall and
downhill season standings. Austria’s Marchel Hirscher leads the
men’s overall ranking with Feuz atop the downhill standings.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
